verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord unto me, Go and get thee a linen girdle, and put it upon thy loins, and put it not in water.
verses.verse_html: 1Thus saith the Lord unto me, Go and get thee a linen girdle, and put it upon thy loins, and put it not in water.

verses.text_plain: So I got a girdle according to the word of the Lord, and put it on my loins.
verses.verse_html: 2So I got a girdle according to the word of the Lord, and put it on my loins.

verses.text_plain: And the word of the Lord came unto me the second time, saying,
verses.verse_html: 3And the word of the Lord came unto me the second time, saying,

tokens.text: came unto me the second time

verses.text_plain: Take the girdle that thou hast got, which is upon thy loins, and arise, go to Euphrates, and hide it there in a hole of the rock.
verses.verse_html: 4Take the girdle that thou hast got, which is upon thy loins, and arise, go to Euphrates, and hide it there in a hole of the rock.

verses.text_plain: So I went, and hid it by Euphrates, as the Lord commanded me.
verses.verse_html: 5So I went, and hid it by Euphrates, as the Lord commanded me.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass after many days, that the Lord said unto me, Arise, go to Euphrates, and take the girdle from thence, which I commanded thee to hide there.
verses.verse_html: 6And it came to pass after many days, that the Lord said unto me, Arise, go to Euphrates, and take the girdle from thence, which I commanded thee to hide there.

tokens.text: And it came to pass after

verses.text_plain: Then I went to Euphrates, and digged, and took the girdle from the place where I had hid it: and, behold, the girdle was marred, it was profitable for nothing.
verses.verse_html: 7Then I went to Euphrates, and digged, and took the girdle from the place where I had hid it: and, behold, the girdle was marred, it was profitable for nothing.

verses.text_plain: Then the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 8Then the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord, After this manner will I mar the pride of Judah, and the great pride of Jerusalem.
verses.verse_html: 9Thus saith the Lord, After this manner will I mar the pride of Judah, and the great pride of Jerusalem.

tokens.text: After this manner will I mar

verses.text_plain: This evil people, which refuse to hear my words, which walk in the imagination of their heart, and walk after other gods, to serve them, and to worship them, shall even be as this girdle, which is good for nothing.
verses.verse_html:
10This evil people, which refuse to hear my words, which walk in the imagination of their heart, and walk after other gods, to serve them, and to worship them, shall even be as this girdle, which is good for nothing.
 imagination: or, stubbornness

tokens.text: them, shall even be as this girdle

verses.text_plain: For as the girdle cleaveth to the loins of a man, so have I caused to cleave unto me the whole house of Israel and the whole house of Judah, saith the Lord; that they might be unto me for a people, and for a name, and for a praise, and for a glory: but they would not hear.
verses.verse_html: 11For as the girdle cleaveth to the loins of a man, so have I caused to cleave unto me the whole house of Israel and the whole house of Judah, saith the Lord; that they might be unto me for a people, and for a name, and for a praise, and for a glory: but they would not hear.

tokens.text: so have I caused to cleave
that they might be unto me for a people

verses.text_plain: Therefore thou shalt speak unto them this word; Thus saith the Lord God of Israel, Every bottle shall be filled with wine: and they shall say unto thee, Do we not certainly know that every bottle shall be filled with wine?
verses.verse_html: 12Therefore thou shalt speak unto them this word; Thus saith the Lord God of Israel, Every bottle shall be filled with wine: and they shall say unto thee, Do we not certainly know that every bottle shall be filled with wine?

tokens.text: unto thee, Do we not certainly

verses.text_plain: Then shalt thou say unto them, Thus saith the Lord, Behold, I will fill all the inhabitants of this land, even the kings that sit upon Davids throne, and the priests, and the prophets, and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, with drunkenness.
verses.verse_html: 13Then shalt thou say unto them, Thus saith the Lord, Behold, I will fill all the inhabitants of this land, even the kings that sit upon Davids throne, and the priests, and the prophets, and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, with drunkenness.

verses.text_plain: And I will dash them one against another, even the fathers and the sons together, saith the Lord: I will not pity, nor spare, nor have mercy, but destroy them.
verses.verse_html:
14And I will dash them one against another, even the fathers and the sons together, saith the Lord: I will not pity, nor spare, nor have mercy, but destroy them.
 one: Heb. a man against his brother
 ,
 but: Heb. from destroying them

footnotes.body_html: one: Heb. a man against his brother

verses.text_plain: Hear ye, and give ear; be not proud: for the Lord hath spoken.
verses.verse_html: 15Hear ye, and give ear; be not proud: for the Lord hath spoken.

verses.text_plain: Give glory to the Lord your God, before he cause darkness, and before your feet stumble upon the dark mountains, and, while ye look for light, he turn it into the shadow of death, and make it gross darkness.
verses.verse_html: 16Give glory to the Lord your God, before he cause darkness, and before your feet stumble upon the dark mountains, and, while ye look for light, he turn it into the shadow of death, and make it gross darkness.

tokens.text: it into the shadow of death

verses.text_plain: But if ye will not hear it, my soul shall weep in secret places for your pride; and mine eye shall weep sore, and run down with tears, because the Lords flock is carried away captive.
verses.verse_html: 17But if ye will not hear it, my soul shall weep in secret places for your pride; and mine eye shall weep sore, and run down with tears, because the Lords flock is carried away captive.

tokens.text: But if ye will not hear

verses.text_plain: Say unto the king and to the queen, Humble yourselves, sit down: for your principalities shall come down, even the crown of your glory.
verses.verse_html:
18Say unto the king and to the queen, Humble yourselves, sit down: for your principalities shall come down, even the crown of your glory.
 principalities: or, head tires

footnotes.body_html: principalities: or, head tires

verses.text_plain: The cities of the south shall be shut up, and none shall open them: Judah shall be carried away captive all of it, it shall be wholly carried away captive.
verses.verse_html: 19The cities of the south shall be shut up, and none shall open them: Judah shall be carried away captive all of it, it shall be wholly carried away captive.

tokens.text: all of it, it shall be wholly

verses.text_plain: Lift up your eyes, and behold them that come from the north: where is the flock that was given thee, thy beautiful flock?
verses.verse_html: 20Lift up your eyes, and behold them that come from the north: where is the flock that was given thee, thy beautiful flock?

verses.text_plain: What wilt thou say when he shall punish thee? for thou hast taught them to be captains, and as chief over thee: shall not sorrows take thee, as a woman in travail?
verses.verse_html:
21What wilt thou say when he shall punish thee? for thou hast taught them to be captains, and as chief over thee: shall not sorrows take thee, as a woman in travail?
 punish: Heb. visit upon

footnotes.body_html: punish: Heb. visit upon

verses.text_plain: And if thou say in thine heart, Wherefore come these things upon me? For the greatness of thine iniquity are thy skirts discovered, and thy heels made bare.
verses.verse_html:
22And if thou say in thine heart, Wherefore come these things upon me? For the greatness of thine iniquity are thy skirts discovered, and thy heels made bare.
 made: or, shall be violently taken away

tokens.text: these things upon me? For the greatness

footnotes.body_text: made: or, shall be violently taken away
footnotes.body_html: made: or, shall be violently taken away

verses.text_plain: Can the Ethiopian change his skin, or the leopard his spots? then may ye also do good, that are accustomed to do evil.
verses.verse_html:
23Can the Ethiopian change his skin, or the leopard his spots? then may ye also do good, that are accustomed to do evil.
 accustomed: Heb. taught

verses.text_plain: Therefore will I scatter them as the stubble that passeth away by the wind of the wilderness.
verses.verse_html: 24Therefore will I scatter them as the stubble that passeth away by the wind of the wilderness.

verses.text_plain: This is thy lot, the portion of thy measures from me, saith the Lord; because thou hast forgotten me, and trusted in falsehood.
verses.verse_html: 25This is thy lot, the portion of thy measures from me, saith the Lord; because thou hast forgotten me, and trusted in falsehood.

verses.text_plain: Therefore will I discover thy skirts upon thy face, that thy shame may appear.
verses.verse_html: 26Therefore will I discover thy skirts upon thy face, that thy shame may appear.

verses.text_plain: I have seen thine adulteries, and thy neighings, the lewdness of thy whoredom, and thine abominations on the hills in the fields. Woe unto thee, O Jerusalem! wilt thou not be made clean? when shall it once be?
verses.verse_html:
27I have seen thine adulteries, and thy neighings, the lewdness of thy whoredom, and thine abominations on the hills in the fields. Woe unto thee, O Jerusalem! wilt thou not be made clean? when shall it once be?
 when: Heb. after when yet?

tokens.text: wilt thou not be made clean
